Rummy and it's variants are very old games. The game is actually a simplified version Mahjong, for which are are
dozens of iterations. That is to say, in that time there have been hundreds of rule changes.

The rules I am using come from https://www.pagat.com/rummy/500rum.html, with the following variations:
  * No jokers
  * 5-10-15 scoring, aces always 15 (5 points 2-9, 10 points J, Q, K, 15 points Ace)
  * Deepest drawn card must be added to a new or existing meld
  * "Going out" must end in discard
  * Two players, one deck

These rules reflect the version of the game that I am most familiar with and the version that, anecdotally, seems to
be the most common in the Northeast.